The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                            Business Briefs
                              
	 Sydney, Feb. 6: BHP Billiton launched a sweetened but hostile $147.4 billion bid for rival miner Rio Tinto on Wednesday, ending months of speculation and setting the stage for the worlds second-largest takeover. The company hopes to sell Rio shareholders its idea of assembling a super miner, supplying the lions share of the worlds industries with millions of tonnes of minerals, but runs the risk of igniting a bidding war with Rios largest shareholder, Aluminum Corp of China.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 6: The Reserve Bank of Indias expert group, which is dealing with the issue of reviving 114,000 sick units in the small and medium sector, will soon finalise its report.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Deepak Fertilisers amp; Petrochemicals Corporation has signed a heads of agreement with Norway-based Yara International for the establishment of a joint venture company to produce and market ammonium nitrate and speciality fertilisers in the country.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Hindustan Unilever (HUL) has bought back over three crore shares of the company worth Rs 626.27 crore from shareholders.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Natco Pharma has acquired the assets of the US-based retail pharmacy firm Newark Drugs for an undisclosed amount.                                                                                                                           
